  <center>
      <h2>Under the Cross</h2><br />
  </center>
  <p>Dear Friends in Christ,</p>

  <p>Please join me in our Lenten journey to Calvary. It begins with Ash Wednesday, February 21st at 7:00pm. Our Lenten midweek services with dinners begin the following Wednesday.</p>

  <p><strong>Services</strong></p>

  <p>The Lenten theme is "Truly, This is the Son of God."</p>

  <p>Ash Wednesday Feb. 21st <em>Nicodemus: Doubted Then Believed</em></p>
  <p>Midweek 1 Wed, Feb 28th <em>Judas Iscariot: Not the Messiah, but God's Son?</em></p>
  <p>Midweek 2 Wed, Mar. 7th <em>Pilate: God's Son, Found Innocent</em></p>
  <p>Midweek 3 Wed, Mar. 14th <em>Simon of Cyrene: The Cross, Now Carried</em></p>
  <p>Midweek 4 Wed, Mar. 21st <em>The Thief: Rejected, Then Believed</em></p>
  <p>Midweek 5 Wed, Mar. 28th <em>The Centurion: Truly, the Son of God</em></p>
  <p>Maunday Thursday April 5th <em>Jesus: Rejected, but the Christ</em></p>
  <p>Good Friday April 6th Tennebrae</p>

  <p>All services begin at 7:00pm. All midweek services, excluding Ash Wednesday and Holy Week services will be proceeded by a dinner beginning at 6:00pm.</p><br />

  <p>May God Bless your journey to the cross,</p>
  <p>Pastor Ross</p>
